Are you looking for a more intimate setting for your New Year’s Eve celebration? Then I have the place for you! @savannahsupperclub is the cutest cozy spot perfect for a lovely intimate date night. The atmosphere is stunning - and they’ve got a great selection of cocktails and wine for you and that special someone.

We started off with the house rolls, they were delicious filled with flavor and steaming hot! We also had their deviled eggs and it’s seriously the best I’ve ever had! 

For the main course we fried one of their house favorites which was the Nashville hot chicken sandwich which had the perfect amount of heat and flavor. We also had the meatloaf, and it’s not like regular old type of dish, this meatloaf was fresh, flavorful, and elevated. 

So if you’re searching for a lovely intimate date night this New Years or for future date nights I highly suggest checking this Chicago gem out! Thanks for having us!

Have you heard the news?! @chefbrookew new menu drops TODAY at @esquirebych ! If you haven’t made a reservation yet I highly suggest you do because this menu is only until May 18th.

Chef Brooke has always been one of my favorite chefs! I am a avid @foodnetwork watcher and seeing her creative culinary creations makes me wish I could cook 😂! From Top Chef, to Guys Grocery Games, to Bobby’s Triple Threat, she continues to shine and be the female boss babe that she is! Having the pleasure to meet her yesterday was amazing! 

Now on to this coastal menu! It’s 🔥 bringing a taste of Cali to Chicago! 

We started off with the Brussels sprouts Cesar salad! It was filled with flavor and so delicious! 

We also sampled the fried crab claw pops and it was amazing! So much delicious crab in one bite! If you’re a seafood lover, like myself, this is for you!

For the main course @nat_gudel and I had the pork shank which was to DIE FOR, and the triple burger which is now ONLY offered at Esquire! 

We finished with the rum & chamomile crème caramel! 

Overall, an amazing menu and I highly suggest checking it out! Thanks @winkpr & @esquirebych for having us!

Here’s your sign to book that romantic trip to @vegas ! Everyone always thinks of Vegas for the bachelorette parties, the gambling, and for the wild nights out.

It can totally be about that, but, if you’re looking to explore it on a romantic side then this video is for you!

Y’all voted and here’s my three day itinerary on what to do in Vegas!

Start off going to @venetianvegas they’ve got so many beautiful views inside literally transporting you to Venice! Do a romantic gondola ride and then end with getting dinner in one of their many delicious Italian restaurants.

Second you can talk a walk around @wynnlasvegas they’ve also great shops and restaurants! I recommend doing lakeside! You’ll get dinner, drinks, and a light show!

Speaking of cocktails and delicious food, I highly recommend checking out @vanderpumpvegas for stunning cocktails! It’s also beautiful inside of there! @spagolv is also stunning! It’s owned by @wolfgangpuck and the views, cocktails, and food is fresh and fantastic! The Chandelier bar also is gorgeous with beautiful 🍹! 

Finish your stay by checking out @hellskitchen in Cesar’s palace! If you’re a fan of @hellskitchenfox and @gordongram then this experience will blow you away! It was the best beef Wellington I’ve ever had! End it with doing the @madamtussauds wax museum for a bunch of fun pictures!

If you’re looking to plan a vacation to Vegas I hope this helps! Feel free to DM me with any questions you may have! Happy FriYAY besties!

Nobody’s putting me back in the BOX. Huge shout out to @alliedglobalmarketing for allowing me to see @barbiethemovie ! It was definitely one of my favorite movies of the year.

Not just for the amazing outfits, y’all see the @chanelofficial and coordinating outfits?! I was obsessed and I need all of Barbie’s clothes! 😂 

But what I loved most of all is the positive message it gave women and young girls! So many times as women, we’re told we’re not enough. 

We’re not pretty enough, thin enough, smart enough, loud enough, nothing is ever good enough. This movie expressed that even in our imperfect moments we’re enough, we’re beautiful, and we can do anything we put our minds too. 

That is SUCH a powerful message especially to young girls. Barbie was the first woman I saw who did everything, she was a doctor, a Nobel piece winner, a fashion icon, and a astronaut. Barbie reacted for the stars and so can we! 

So remember that in your most vulnerable moments, that you are ENOUGH!
